<br>
Last night at Vulak, I was outdamaged by a necro.  Sure, it was the best equipped necro in EQ (but my equipment isn't shabby either).  Sure, she set the rules before hand:  No mod rods, no mana pumps, no bard song.  Just my mana regen resources vs. hers.  Mine = FT2 + Epic + Mana robe (c2 + gob as well, to be fair).  Hers = Demi-Lich.<br>
<br>
The result?  She outdamaged me.  Barely, yes.. but it came as a little bit of a shocker.  It was a quick Vulak fight - only about 15 mins or so.  Plus, I haven't seen her logs yet, just the number of spells she casted vs. the number of peridots I used.  <br>
<br>
I won't post any numbers here just yet.  We're gonna try this a few more times and see what we come up with - this may have been a fluke or whatever.  Plus I'd like to get an average.  Sorta strange isn't it?  Being outdamaged by a necro isn't something we normally deal with at that stage of the game ...<br>
<br>
Comments? <p><font color="#FFFFFF" face="Tahoma" size="2"><a href="http://foh.noows.com/showthread.php?s=&threadid=1590">Frozboz D'Sospes</a> | <a href="http://www.noows.com">Fires of Heaven</a></font>
